The school group were seated with their chaperones at the back of the plane and assigned adult standard seated which should hold a standard 87kg adult.

The children were all over the age of 11 which is above the age child seats are assigned.

There was quite a serious discrepancy of 55kg per seat each child was was assigned to while majority of the adult passengers were given seats at the front of plane.

The aircraft appeared nose-heavy during take-off, forcing the captain to apply significant back pressure to achieve lift off from the runway.

