Too much back pressure could have caused the aircraft tail to strike the runway, but the captain managed to ease the aircraft into the air.

The incident, prompted an investigation by the Australian Transport Safety Bureau.

It was subsequently determined that the final load sheet overstated the aircraft take-off weight by about 3.5 to five tonnes.

The Australian Transport and Safety Bureau said Qantas issued a new procedure to check-in staff, reminding them to ensure that children travelling on group bookings must be recorded as children, to ensure aircraft weight and balance is based on an accurate passenger type.

